  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>--bg-primary: #030712;</code> (Deep black background)</li>
    <li><code>--bg-secondary: #0b0f19;</code> (Dark blue panels)</li>
    <li><code>--bg-glass: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);</code> (Translucent glass panels)</li>
    <li><code>--accent-indigo: #6366f1;</code> (Primary accent color)</li>
    <li><code>--accent-purple: #a855f7;</code> (Secondary accent color)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Panels use backdrop filters (<code>backdrop-filter: blur(25px) saturate(180%)</code>) to create a translucent frosted-glass effect over the floating mesh background.
  </p>

  <h2>6.2. High-Performance 3D Card Hover Tilts</h2>
  <p>
    To improve the user experience, metric and call cards tilt in 3D space when hovered. To avoid performance issues from binding multiple event listeners to dynamic elements, the app uses a single event delegation handler on <code>document.body</code>:
  </p>
  <pre>
document.addEventListener('mousemove', (e) => {
  const card = e.target.closest('.tilt-3d');
  if (card) {
    const rect = card.getBoundingClientRect();
    const x = e.clientX - rect.left;
    const y = e.clientY - rect.top;
    const xc = rect.width / 2;
    const yc = rect.height / 2;
    const maxTilt = 8;
    const tiltX = ((yc - y) / yc) * maxTilt;
    const tiltY = ((x - xc) / xc) * maxTilt;
    card.style.transform = `perspective(1000px) rotateX(${tiltX}deg) rotateY(${tiltY}deg) scale3d(1.02, 1.02, 1.02)`;
  }
});
  </pre>

